The '''Kachirho Bridge''' was a large bridge connecting two portions of one of the [[Tree/Legends|tree]]-[[City/Legends|cities]] of [[Kachirho/Legends|Kachirho]] on [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk's]] [[Wawaatt Archipelago/Legends|Wawaatt Archipelago]].

==History==
The bridge at Kachirho became a critical target during the initial invasion of Kashyyyk by [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] forces towards the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The elite [[Clone commando/Legends|Clone commandos]] of [[Delta Squad/Legends|Delta Squad]] were dispatched to defend the bridge. After pushing back a brigade of [[B2-series super battle droid/Legends|Super Battle Droids]] amidst debris and the strewn-about bodies of [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]], Delta's objective was to destroy the bridge and stop the forward advance of the Separatist forces. Delta attempted to blow the bridge from a weak stop in the middle, however the explosives misfired. The resourceful Deltas were able to destroy the bridge by targeting a fuel line that ran under the center span of the bridge, with a [[Wookiee Guided Rocket Launcher]], there-by succeeding in delaying the droid invasion in time for a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] counter-offensive at the Home Tree.

==Behind the scenes==
In the video game, ''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando]]'', the player has the option of destroying the fuel line underneath the Kachirho Bridge by using the anti-armor attachment of the [[DC-17m Interchangeable Weapon System/Legends|DC-17m]], as opposed to using the Wookiee Guided Rocket Launcher.

